vania)|James Cooper]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Rhode Island|Rhode Island]] ====\n* 1. [[Charles Tillinghast James|Charles T. James]] (D)\n* 2. [[John Hopkins Clarke|John H. Clarke]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from South Carolina|South Carolina]] ====\n* 2. [[Robert Rhett]] (D), until May 7, 1852\n** [[William F. De Saussure]] (D), from May 10, 1852\n* 3. [[Andrew Butler]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Tennessee|Tennessee]] ====\n* 1. [[James C. Jones]] (W)\n* 2. [[John Bell (Tennessee politician)|John Bell]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Texas|Texas]] ====\n* 1. [[Thomas Jefferson Rusk|Thomas J. Rusk]] (D)\n* 2. [[Sam Houston]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Vermont|Vermont]] ====\n* 1. [[Solomon Foot]] (W)\n* 3. [[William Upham]] (W), until January 14, 1853\n** [[Samuel S. Phelps]] (W), from January 17, 1853\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Virginia|Virginia]] ====\n* 1. [[James Murray Mason|James M. Mason]] (D)\n* 2. [[Robert Mercer Taliaferro Hunter|Robert M. T. Hunter]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Wisconsin|Wisconsin]] ====\n* 1. [[Henry Dodge]] (D)\n* 3. [[Isaac P. Walker]] (D)\n{{col-end}}\n\n=== House of Representatives===\nThe names of members of the House of Representatives are preceded by their district numbers.\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Alabama|Alabama]] ====\n* {{ushr|Alabama|1|1}}. [[John Bragg (politician)|John Bragg]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Alabama|2|2}}. [[James Abercrombie (Congressman)|James Abercrombie]] (W)\n* {{ushr|Alabama|3|3}}. [[Sampson Willis Harris|Sampson W. Harris]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Alabama|4|4}}. [[William Russell Smith|William R. Smith]] (U)\n* {{ushr|Alabama|5|5}}. [[George S. Houston]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Alabama|6|6}}. [[Williamson Robert Winfield Cobb|Williamson R. W. Cobb]] (D)\n* {{ushr|Alabama|7|7}}. [[Alexander White (Alabama)|Alexander White]] (W)\n\n===